@startuml sequence_batch_tailor
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Sequence — Batch Tailor Multiple Roles (batch-tailor.ps1)

actor Candidate
participant "batch-tailor.ps1" as Batch
participant "Job Pool\n(max 4 concurrent)" as Pool
participant "new-variant.ps1" as NewVariant
participant "Claude Code\nTailoring Prompt" as Claude

Candidate -> Batch : Invoke: batch-tailor.ps1 -Roles [role1, role2, ...]

Batch -> Batch : Parse role list;\nrecord start time

loop While roles remaining or jobs running
    Batch -> Pool : Enqueue next role (if slots available)
    Pool -> NewVariant : Start background job:\nnew-variant.ps1 -Name <slug>
    NewVariant --> Pool : Variant file created

    Pool -> Claude : Invoke tailoring prompt\nfor <slug>
    Claude --> Pool : Tailored variant written

    Pool --> Batch : Job complete: exit code + elapsed time
    Batch -> Batch : Record JobResult\n(succeeded or failed)
end

Batch -> Batch : Compute total elapsed time
Batch --> Candidate : Print BatchReport:\nSucceeded: N | Failed: M\nTotal time: Xs\nFailed roles: [list]

@enduml
